WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:00.232 --> 01:04.446
Trees have a secret life
that is only revealed

01:04.447 --> 01:06.342
to those who are willing
to climb them.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.094
I do not remember
when I was born.

01:24.147 --> 01:25.728
But, when I was three
months old,

01:25.728 --> 01:28.467
my mother returned
to my grandparents' home

01:28.467 --> 01:30.995
with me as the proof
of her failure.

01:53.120 --> 01:56.702
The splendor of my childhood
was unique,

01:57.439 --> 02:02.391
because of its absolute poverty,
and absolute freedom...

02:04.076 --> 02:05.867
out in the open,

02:05.867 --> 02:09.344
surrounded by trees,
animals, and people

02:09.345 --> 02:11.767
who were indifferent
toward me.

02:21.565 --> 02:23.567
Reinaldo!

02:24.937 --> 02:26.728
Reinaldo!

02:29.572 --> 02:31.995
Niño, apúrate con esa agua,
Dios mío!

02:31.996 --> 02:33.892
Mira que hay que esperar
en esta casa!

02:33.892 --> 02:37.684
My early life was surrounded
by a room full of unhappy women

02:37.685 --> 02:41.161
who were all bossed around
by my grandmother,

02:41.162 --> 02:44.216
the heart of the house,

02:44.217 --> 02:47.272
the only woman I ever saw
who peed standing up

02:47.273 --> 02:49.800
and talked to God
at the same time.

02:51.170 --> 02:55.700
My mother was a very beautiful
and very lonely woman.

02:55.701 --> 02:58.650
She had only known one man,
my father,

02:58.651 --> 03:03.075
and had enjoyed the pleasures
of love for only a few months

03:03.076 --> 03:07.921
and then, gave that all up
for the rest of her life,

03:07.922 --> 03:12.346
creating in her
a great sense of frustration.

03:12.347 --> 03:15.190
Her chastity was worse
than that of a virgin.

03:15.191 --> 03:16.981
Hijo de puta!

03:16.982 --> 03:19.088
Vete de aquí!

03:20.247 --> 03:21.933
Animal!

03:35.524 --> 03:37.736
Hijo de puta!

03:43.531 --> 03:45.216
Desgraciado!

03:45.216 --> 03:47.955
The most extraordinary
event of my childhood

03:47.956 --> 03:50.063
was provided by the heavens.

03:50.063 --> 03:53.181
Water rushed down gutters,

03:53.183 --> 03:56.820
reverberating over
the zinc roof like gunfire

03:56.821 --> 03:59.835
a massive army marching
across the trees,

03:59.836 --> 04:05.553
overflowing, cascading,
thundering into barrels,

04:05.554 --> 04:07.737
a concert of drums,

04:07.737 --> 04:09.712
water falling on water,

04:09.713 --> 04:13.039
drenched and whistling
and out of control,

04:13.040 --> 04:15.222
and under the spell of violence,

04:15.223 --> 04:20.005
let loose that would sweep away
almost everything in its path.

04:20.005 --> 04:23.851
Trees, stones,
animals, houses.

04:23.853 --> 04:26.866
It was the mystery
of destruction.

04:26.868 --> 04:28.634
The law of life.

04:28.634 --> 04:30.297
As I saw it,

04:30.401 --> 04:32.897
the currents were
roaring my name.

04:36.223 --> 04:39.758
Flowers have
reproductive organs.

04:39.758 --> 04:44.749
Class, can anyone
tell us what the male

04:44.750 --> 04:47.764
reproductive organ is called?

04:50.883 --> 04:52.650
Reinaldo?

04:53.794 --> 04:55.249
Reinaldo?

04:55.249 --> 04:58.368
A dick.
A long, skinny dick.

05:05.854 --> 05:08.245
Don't ask her where
she comes from.

05:08.246 --> 05:11.260
Can't you see she
is from the garden

05:11.261 --> 05:14.899
and the most beautiful
flower of them all?

05:56.381 --> 05:58.772
Buenas tardes,
con permiso.

05:59.812 --> 06:02.931
Señor Fuentes, I didn't mean
to disturb your dinner.

06:02.932 --> 06:04.179
What did he do?

06:04.283 --> 06:06.882
No, he didn't do
anything wrong.

06:06.883 --> 06:11.248
I came here to tell you that
Reinaldo has a special gift.

06:12.496 --> 06:14.055
What special gift?

06:14.159 --> 06:17.070
He has a sensitivity
for poetry.

07:15.395 --> 07:17.579
After that, my grandfather
sold the farm

07:17.580 --> 07:20.490
and moved the family
to Holguín,

07:20.491 --> 07:22.569
opened a grocery store,

07:22.569 --> 07:24.856
and refused to speak
to any of us.

07:30.367 --> 07:33.185
Holguín was a town
of 200,000 people

07:33.185 --> 07:35.273
and one garbage truck.

07:56.567 --> 08:00.011
The rebels are in Velasco.

08:00.012 --> 08:01.890
We can walk it in a day.

08:01.891 --> 08:03.873
Okay.

08:03.874 --> 08:05.857
We'll leave tonight.

08:05.858 --> 08:07.318
'Tá bien.

08:07.318 --> 08:10.554
You think you can
do it with her?

08:10.555 --> 08:12.850
My name is Reinaldo.
What is yours?

08:12.851 --> 08:14.103
Loly.

08:14.207 --> 08:16.921
- Would you like to dance?
- Cómo no.

08:36.232 --> 08:38.528
¿Qué tú quieres?
Tú eres muy niño.

08:42.285 --> 08:45.417
Incorpórate a la lucha.

08:45.418 --> 08:51.158
Radio Rebelde, transmitiendo
desde las montañas de Oriente,

08:51.159 --> 08:53.664
desde la Sierra Maestra,

08:53.665 --> 08:56.691
territorio libre de Cuba.

08:56.692 --> 08:58.674
Aquí Radio Rebelde.

10:27.399 --> 10:29.382
Where are you going, kid?

10:29.383 --> 10:32.096
- Up the road.
- Up the road where?

10:32.097 --> 10:33.140
Velasco.

10:34.810 --> 10:37.628
Velasco?
You are not from Velasco.

10:37.629 --> 10:42.326
I am from Velasco.
Why do you go to Velasco for?

10:42.327 --> 10:45.770
Ah, the rebels
are in Velasco.

10:45.771 --> 10:47.545
You going to join
the rebels?

10:47.545 --> 10:51.511
Your mamá know you are
going to join the rebels?

10:51.512 --> 10:52.868
No.

10:52.868 --> 10:54.121
No.

10:54.121 --> 10:55.687
Where she is?

10:55.687 --> 10:57.879
She's in Miami, working.

10:57.879 --> 11:07.899
Would you like to see?

11:07.900 --> 11:11.970
It's upside down.

11:11.971 --> 11:13.432
Qué bonita.

11:19.173 --> 11:20.843
You want to hit things?

11:23.243 --> 11:27.106
Sometimes I like
to hit things.

11:27.107 --> 11:32.533
My mother, she has
a store in Velasco.

11:32.535 --> 11:35.978
Before that it was my
grandmother's store,

11:35.979 --> 11:38.588
and before that,
it was her mother's store.

11:38.589 --> 11:40.153
I have six brothers.

11:40.153 --> 11:43.911
They all want
to join the rebels.

11:43.912 --> 11:46.625
The second one,
he joined the rebels.

11:46.626 --> 11:51.218
I'm the middle one,
I don't join the rebels.

11:57.690 --> 11:59.568
Get that for me.

12:12.094 --> 12:13.764
Go home.

12:14.808 --> 12:17.105
The rebels are no more
in Velasco.

12:17.105 --> 12:19.192
Go on, get off.

12:19.297 --> 12:20.654
Get off!

12:22.637 --> 12:24.307
What?
What?

12:49.672 --> 12:51.968
Que viva Fidel!

12:51.969 --> 12:53.534
Viva Fidel!

12:53.534 --> 12:54.578
Cuba libre!

15:26.767 --> 15:28.229
Translator: Es todo por hoy.

15:28.229 --> 15:29.690
Spaziva!

15:49.836 --> 15:53.489
As my mother smacked me,
she cursed

15:53.490 --> 15:56.621
and yelled, "Maldito!
Bad seed!"

15:56.622 --> 15:59.230
She shouted at the sky,
"I want to get out of here. "

15:59.231 --> 16:02.466
But I really wasn't sure
that's what she wanted.

16:07.790 --> 16:11.339
But now standing over me

16:11.339 --> 16:13.426
she looked like
a huge tree trunk.

16:13.844 --> 16:18.854
And if it didn't hurt so much,
I'd get down on my knees,

16:18.855 --> 16:21.986
and ask her to smack me again,
even harder.

16:23.238 --> 16:25.535
Then she became beautiful.

16:25.536 --> 16:29.397
How pretty she is in her skirt
made out of a sack

16:29.398 --> 16:32.424
and the blouse she stole
from her sister.

16:32.425 --> 16:35.138
I wanted to get up and beg
her forgiveness.

16:35.138 --> 16:39.939
I wanted to say,
"Mom, how pretty you are today.

16:39.940 --> 16:41.505
You look like
one of those women

16:41.505 --> 16:43.697
that you can only see
on Christmas cards, "

16:43.697 --> 16:48.812
but I said nothing because
of the the knot in my throat.

16:51.317 --> 16:54.448
That was very nice.
What's your name?

16:54.448 --> 16:56.014
Reinaldo Arenas.

16:56.015 --> 16:57.580
Who wrote this?

16:57.580 --> 17:00.085
I did, it's my own--
from my novel.

17:00.085 --> 17:01.860
What do you call this novel?

17:01.860 --> 17:03.634
"Singing from the Well. "

17:03.635 --> 17:05.095
Are you a student?

17:05.095 --> 17:08.749
Yes, I'm an agricultural
accountant.

17:13.968 --> 17:16.578
Tell me, do you think
you'd feel at home

17:16.578 --> 17:18.455
working in the national library?

17:18.457 --> 17:20.440
The pay won't be very much.

17:20.441 --> 17:23.362
But I can promise you
that you'll have all the books

17:23.363 --> 17:25.137
you could ever hope to read.

17:25.137 --> 17:27.016
I would like that
very much.

17:27.017 --> 17:28.373
Thank you very much.

17:32.339 --> 17:32.861
Thank you.

17:48.414 --> 17:51.650
Oye, need a lift?

17:51.650 --> 17:53.216
I want to go down
to Guayanos.

17:53.216 --> 17:55.303
Get in.

17:57.391 --> 17:58.957
Hello.

18:03.967 --> 18:05.742
Driver: You like it, right?

18:06.159 --> 18:09.291
It used to belong
to Errol Flynn.

18:10.752 --> 18:12.109
You don't believe me?

18:12.213 --> 18:13.779
Look in the glove
compartment.

18:18.789 --> 18:21.190
Be careful, huh?

18:22.860 --> 18:25.261
Do you want to go
to the movies with me?

18:25.262 --> 18:26.305
What?

18:26.409 --> 18:28.079
Do you want to go
to the movies with me?

18:28.079 --> 18:30.689
- I'll get out here!
- Ay, coño!

18:34.864 --> 18:37.369
You got a flat ass anyway!

18:37.683 --> 18:39.666
Vamos, chico, vamos!

18:39.667 --> 18:42.067
You'll see him tomorrow.

18:42.068 --> 18:43.945
Get out!

18:50.522 --> 18:52.192
Estúpido!

18:55.636 --> 18:58.554
... last Saturday night
I made 100 pesos

18:58.555 --> 19:01.368
for letting 10 members
of the National Ballet

19:01.369 --> 19:02.514
suck me off.

19:03.660 --> 19:05.744
Doesn't that make you a fag?

19:05.744 --> 19:08.037
If you do it for money,
you're not a fag.

19:44.196 --> 19:46.593
You know him?

19:46.593 --> 19:47.635
No.

19:53.367 --> 19:54.304
Hello.

19:54.304 --> 19:55.659
I'm sorry about the other day.

19:55.763 --> 19:56.805
No, don't worry.
Forget it.

19:56.805 --> 19:58.890
- I am Reinaldo.
- I am Pepe.

19:58.891 --> 20:00.869
- How about some ice cream?
- Yes!

20:00.869 --> 20:03.058
Today they have only vanilla.

20:03.891 --> 20:07.226
Bring him a banana split
with pistacho.

20:07.226 --> 20:08.998
One ice cream!

20:09.519 --> 20:10.352
Go.

20:11.290 --> 20:14.208
So where you from,
Reinaldo?

20:14.209 --> 20:16.396
I am a guajiro,
from Oriente.

20:16.397 --> 20:18.376
- Does it matter where I'm from?
- No.

20:18.377 --> 20:19.731
What do you do?

20:19.835 --> 20:22.649
I just got a job now
in the National Library,

20:22.650 --> 20:25.358
but I would like to be
a writer.

20:26.921 --> 20:29.735
You poor thing.

20:29.736 --> 20:32.340
A country boy in Havana
to serve the Revolution.

20:49.117 --> 20:51.618
- Where's your mother?
- En la bodega.

20:51.619 --> 20:53.494
Give me the key.

20:53.494 --> 20:55.265
Chau.

20:55.266 --> 20:56.203
Vamos!

21:11.209 --> 21:13.293
She says it works,

21:13.293 --> 21:15.585
just one key is a little off.

21:15.586 --> 21:17.774
How can I thank you?

21:22.255 --> 21:23.609
What are you doing?

21:23.610 --> 21:24.964
Who is the man?

21:26.423 --> 21:28.299
Who's the man?

21:28.300 --> 21:31.008
You, because you are
the judo expert.

21:36.114 --> 21:38.823
You don't kiss
on the lips?

21:38.824 --> 21:41.324
Only when I'm in love.

21:44.972 --> 21:48.828
Patricio Lamumba Beach is only
a 10 minute walk from here--

21:48.829 --> 21:51.851
La Concha is about a mile...

21:51.851 --> 21:53.831
This is perfect for you.

21:53.831 --> 21:58.000
You'll have to share
the bathroom with her.

21:58.001 --> 22:00.293
Bedsheets are changed
every two weeks

22:00.293 --> 22:03.316
and you are responsible
for your own towel.

22:03.733 --> 22:05.609
It is perfect, I'll take it.

22:05.610 --> 22:08.111
Don't you want to know
how much?

22:08.111 --> 22:10.091
It doesn't matter,
I can not afford it anyway.

22:10.091 --> 22:12.593
30 pesos a month--

22:13.843 --> 22:16.970
and no visitors...

22:16.971 --> 22:18.951
nor music after 10:00pm.

22:19.680 --> 22:20.931
30.

22:29.374 --> 22:31.458
Thank you.

22:53.764 --> 22:55.848
National Book Award Contest.

23:00.747 --> 23:02.415
Hello.

23:02.415 --> 23:04.082
I would like
to submit this please.

23:04.187 --> 23:05.542
Put it in the box.

26:18.472 --> 26:20.765
Hey, you want a smoke?

26:20.766 --> 26:21.912
No, thank you.

26:34.524 --> 26:37.651
What are you reading?

26:37.652 --> 26:39.839
Este es "El Lazarillo
de Tormes. "

26:39.839 --> 26:41.299
Who wrote it?

26:44.530 --> 26:45.885
No author,
he's anonymous.

26:48.074 --> 26:52.139
No writer?
That's impossible.

26:52.140 --> 26:53.598
No, no, no,
I didn't say no writer.

26:53.598 --> 26:55.370
I said we don't know
who the author is.

26:56.933 --> 27:01.102
Okay.
Do you have any other books?

27:01.103 --> 27:03.083
Yes, I have many.

27:05.167 --> 27:08.190
I usually read out here
so I can be alone.

27:08.190 --> 27:10.900
I like it here.

27:10.900 --> 27:13.089
Sorry to bother you.
I'll leave.

27:13.089 --> 27:15.278
It's okay.
I'm going home anyway.

27:23.199 --> 27:24.971
You live around here?

27:24.971 --> 27:27.577
Not far.

27:28.202 --> 27:30.495
You want to come over
and hear some music?

27:30.495 --> 27:33.205
What?

27:33.206 --> 27:34.873
I have some
French records.

27:34.873 --> 27:35.915
Maybe you like...

27:38.730 --> 27:42.586
Edith Piaf,
and Jacques Brel.

27:45.609 --> 27:47.276
Pero estúpido idiota!

27:47.276 --> 27:49.778
Are you out of your mind?

27:49.779 --> 27:50.924
Take the book with you.

27:51.863 --> 27:54.573
Ojalá se te caiga
la pinga, maricón!

27:54.574 --> 27:56.657
Estúpido!
Coño.

28:00.409 --> 28:02.181
And so, ladies and gentlemen,

28:02.182 --> 28:06.351
we have arrived at this
auspicious moment.

28:06.352 --> 28:10.416
We are happy to announce
that the first prize goes to,

28:10.417 --> 28:14.272
"Vivir en Candonga"
by Ezequiel Vieta.

28:27.092 --> 28:31.991
And the honorable mention
goes to Reinaldo Arenas

28:31.992 --> 28:34.076
for "Celestino Antes de Alba. "

28:42.831 --> 28:44.290
Thank you.
Gracias.

28:45.541 --> 28:47.730
Thank you for coming
ladies and gentlemen,

28:47.731 --> 28:50.753
and another round of applause
for our contestants.

29:00.133 --> 29:01.280
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

29:01.384 --> 29:03.156
You're invited to
Lezama Lima's house.

29:14.413 --> 29:15.976
Hello.

29:41.409 --> 29:45.369
He left after his brother
made the film "P. M. "

29:45.371 --> 29:46.724
You've heard about it.

29:46.725 --> 29:49.434
The brother had to leave, too.

29:49.435 --> 29:51.102
Simple film.

29:53.916 --> 29:57.252
Just a group of people
dancing and getting drunk.

29:58.919 --> 30:01.734
It made no judgments.

30:03.089 --> 30:05.069
It made no judgments.

30:06.216 --> 30:11.427
People that make art are
dangerous to any dictatorship.

30:14.450 --> 30:16.847
They create beauty.

30:18.306 --> 30:20.912
And beauty is the enemy.

30:21.329 --> 30:24.247
Artists are escapists.

30:24.664 --> 30:27.270
Artists are counter-
revolutionary,

30:27.271 --> 30:32.065
and so you are a counter-
revolutionary, Reinaldo Arenas,

30:32.066 --> 30:33.420
and you know why?

30:35.400 --> 30:40.090
Because there's a man
that cannot govern

30:40.091 --> 30:43.009
the terrain called beauty,
so he wants to eliminate it.

30:43.010 --> 30:46.400
So, here we are, 400 years
of Cuban culture

30:46.401 --> 30:49.791
about to become extinct
and everybody applauds.

30:49.791 --> 30:51.187
And what happened to your lip?

30:52.085 --> 30:55.077
I found somebody who doesn't
like French music, that's all.

30:55.078 --> 30:56.972
Be careful.
Be careful.

30:56.972 --> 30:59.365
No, no, no.
Keep it--

30:59.366 --> 31:01.160
He would love for you
to have it.

31:02.457 --> 31:06.047
There are 150 books that
contain everything

31:06.047 --> 31:07.942
that literature has to offer.

31:07.942 --> 31:10.535
You read them and you don't have
to read anything else.

31:10.535 --> 31:12.330
So which book would
be the first?

31:12.331 --> 31:14.933
"The Bible. "
You have to read the Bible.

31:14.934 --> 31:17.535
Oh, croquettes.
Ooh, María Luisa.

31:22.220 --> 31:26.800
These croquettes don't stick
to the roof of your mouth.

31:29.090 --> 31:30.756
They are delicious.

31:30.756 --> 31:31.797
What kind are they?

31:31.797 --> 31:33.254
I n this country, you don't
ask that question.

31:33.256 --> 31:35.649
We're all being placed
on an international diet.

31:35.650 --> 31:36.690
Let's go back
to the Bible,

31:36.794 --> 31:38.980
it's far
more interesting.

31:38.980 --> 31:42.207
Now, I don't mean
to convert you.

31:42.207 --> 31:43.769
Just read it like a novel.

31:43.770 --> 31:47.308
I tell you what, I'm going
to give you five books--

31:47.309 --> 31:50.223
Correction, I'm going to lend
you five books.

31:50.224 --> 31:53.346
You return them,
then I'll give you five more.

31:53.347 --> 31:55.532
"Moby Dick, " Melville,

31:55.533 --> 31:58.447
Robert Lewis Stevenson's
"Treasure lsland, "

31:58.448 --> 32:00.945
Proust's,
"Remembrance of Things Past"

32:00.946 --> 32:03.235
Kafka's "Metamorphosis, "

32:03.235 --> 32:05.630
Flaubert's,
"Sentimental Education. "

32:06.358 --> 32:08.440
María Luisa,
coffee please.

32:09.794 --> 32:11.771
One, two, three--

32:11.772 --> 32:14.999
four, five.

32:15.000 --> 32:18.122
Reinaldo, I don't mean
to be presumptuous,

32:18.122 --> 32:19.787
but we've read your book.

32:19.788 --> 32:22.286
We both think
it's far superior

32:22.287 --> 32:23.951
to the one
that won first prize.

32:23.952 --> 32:25.929
They robbed you
of the first prize.

32:25.929 --> 32:27.595
But, to be frank,

32:27.595 --> 32:29.989
there's always room
for improvement.

32:31.342 --> 32:33.008
If you'll allow,

32:33.008 --> 32:36.131
Virgilio would like
to help you clean it up.

32:36.132 --> 32:38.213
Right now it's good,

32:38.213 --> 32:40.711
but it's too good
not to be great.

32:40.711 --> 32:42.065
Let's fix it.

32:42.065 --> 32:44.771
Second prize
gets published too.

32:44.772 --> 32:46.333
That's the real prize.

32:46.334 --> 32:49.143
We both think that
you were born to write.

33:02.156 --> 33:04.134
You can't be too careful.

33:04.134 --> 33:08.194
This is the only possession
that you really need.

33:08.818 --> 33:11.213
... de la vida.

33:21.623 --> 33:23.809
Las lagartijas son muy grandes
en este bañado.

33:23.913 --> 33:25.370
Si tú las vieras!
Las lagartijas...

