now and then,

40:46.376 --> 40:48.365
only has relations
with other gays,

40:48.365 --> 40:49.832
never takes a risk,

40:49.832 --> 40:52.032
and never gets
to know a real man.

40:52.241 --> 40:54.441
The third one,

40:54.441 --> 40:55.698
the closet gay,
okay,

40:55.803 --> 40:57.060
nobody knows
he is gay.

40:57.060 --> 40:59.469
He's married,
has children,

40:59.470 --> 41:01.564
hides on his way
to the bathroom,

41:01.565 --> 41:04.393
still wearing the ring
that his wife gave him.

41:04.393 --> 41:07.326
They're hard to spot,
but I've got one here.

41:11.307 --> 41:13.926
Most of the time they're
the ones who censor other gays.

41:22.306 --> 41:23.249
And fourth, the royal gay,

41:23.249 --> 41:25.030
a unique product
of our country,

41:25.030 --> 41:26.182
a communist country.

41:26.182 --> 41:30.791
Because of his closeness
to our Maximum Leader

41:30.792 --> 41:32.677
or special work with
the State Security,

41:32.677 --> 41:35.924
he can afford
to be openly gay,

41:35.924 --> 41:38.962
travel freely in this
country and abroad,

41:38.963 --> 41:41.686
cover himself
with jewels, clothes...

41:41.686 --> 41:45.667
Coño, he even has
a private chauffeur.

41:51.952 --> 41:54.990
Hey, hey.
Stop!

41:54.990 --> 41:56.666
Reinaldo!

41:56.667 --> 41:58.342
Hey, Reinaldo!

41:58.342 --> 42:01.066
Come on.
We'll give you a ride.

42:05.780 --> 42:07.770
Where are you going?

42:07.771 --> 42:08.713
Don't worry.
Take a seat.

42:10.180 --> 42:12.694
Hello.

42:12.695 --> 42:13.741
How are you?

42:18.560 --> 42:22.855
Now, we're going to take
a little shortcut

42:22.856 --> 42:25.160
and show you a beautiful
part of Havana

42:25.161 --> 42:27.779
that not many
visitors get to see.

43:49.593 --> 43:52.422
The crackdown began in earnest.

43:52.423 --> 43:55.460
The horror and ugliness
advanced day by day

43:55.460 --> 43:57.555
at an ever increasing pace,

43:57.555 --> 44:01.850
but the oppression only
acted as a stimulus

44:02.374 --> 44:04.783
and sex became a way
of fighting it...

44:04.783 --> 44:07.821
a weapon to use
against the regimen.

45:45.559 --> 45:47.025
Needless to say,

45:47.025 --> 45:49.749
the Revolution wasn't
for everybody.

45:49.750 --> 45:53.510
Mr. Heberto Zorrilla Ochoa,

45:53.510 --> 45:58.733
are you aware of Article 243
in the Penal Code?

45:58.734 --> 45:59.569
Yes.

46:00.300 --> 46:04.687
And what does Article 243
of the Penal Code state?

46:04.688 --> 46:09.075
It states that no assembly
of over three people is allowed.

46:09.076 --> 46:13.671
And yet, you had an assembly
of over 20 people at your home

46:13.672 --> 46:15.238
on the night of July 10th.

46:15.239 --> 46:17.118
What were you doing?

46:17.119 --> 46:19.312
It was a poetry reading.

46:19.313 --> 46:21.506
Whose poetry?

46:21.507 --> 46:24.431
My own--
others.

46:24.432 --> 46:28.087
And are you sure that
this was a poetry reading

46:28.087 --> 46:30.281
and not just an
opportunity to recite

46:30.282 --> 46:32.579
counterrevolutionary
propaganda?

46:33.310 --> 46:34.877
Yes, I'm sure.

46:34.877 --> 46:39.683
Mr. Correa, is poetry
ever propaganda?

46:40.727 --> 46:43.130
I suppose it could be.

46:43.131 --> 46:45.950
But not your poetry.

46:45.951 --> 46:48.040
No.

46:48.353 --> 46:52.323
Mr. Correa, who else
was present

46:52.323 --> 46:54.725
at this so-called
poetry reading?

46:56.606 --> 46:59.949
Some friends,
other writers.

46:59.950 --> 47:05.276
Tell me, does the name
José Lezama Lima ring a bell?

47:05.277 --> 47:07.574
Virgilio Piñera?

47:07.574 --> 47:09.873
Your wife, Fina?

47:10.604 --> 47:11.753
Yes.

47:11.857 --> 47:13.215
Were they there?

47:13.216 --> 47:15.305
Yes, they were there.

47:15.306 --> 47:18.752
Are you aware
that Lezama Lima

47:18.753 --> 47:21.677
and Virgilio Piñera
are homosexuals?

47:22.617 --> 47:24.289
