01:38:18.593 --> 01:38:20.049
Maybe.

01:38:30.762 --> 01:38:32.114
Next.

01:38:37.730 --> 01:38:38.666
What's your name?

01:38:38.667 --> 01:38:40.330
Reinaldo Arenas.

01:38:40.434 --> 01:38:43.554
State your reason
for wanting to leave.

01:38:43.555 --> 01:38:46.362
I am homosexual.

01:38:47.298 --> 01:38:49.690
Where do you go
to pick up men.

01:38:54.059 --> 01:38:56.776
En la parada del Hotel Plaza,
en "El Prado, " en "La Sortija. "

01:38:57.612 --> 01:38:59.597
What position do
you like in bed?

01:39:03.150 --> 01:39:06.076
I like it from behind,
and on my knees.

01:39:06.703 --> 01:39:07.957
Walk!

01:39:15.794 --> 01:39:17.048
- Walk! Walk!
- Walk.

01:39:26.662 --> 01:39:28.856
Report to Abreu Fontan.

01:40:10.759 --> 01:40:12.222
What are they doing?

01:40:12.326 --> 01:40:14.312
They got a list
of everyone

01:40:14.313 --> 01:40:15.775
they don't want
to let out.

01:40:19.536 --> 01:40:20.581
Like who?

01:40:20.581 --> 01:40:21.731
I don't know.

01:40:25.702 --> 01:40:28.523
- Do you have a pen?
- No.

01:40:31.658 --> 01:40:33.434
- Do you have a pen?
- No, sir.

01:40:55.796 --> 01:40:57.573
Avancen, avancen,
avancen!

01:43:51.245 --> 01:43:53.126
I don't care where I sleep.

01:43:53.127 --> 01:43:57.410
Just promise me you won't
bring any of your friends here.

01:43:57.410 --> 01:43:59.187
I can cook.
It's no problem.

01:43:59.188 --> 01:44:00.963
How much is it?

01:44:00.964 --> 01:44:03.366
$350 per month,
plus utilities.

01:44:03.367 --> 01:44:05.143
The difference between
the communist system,

01:44:05.143 --> 01:44:06.501
and the capitalist system,

01:44:06.502 --> 01:44:09.218
is that when they give
you a kick in the ass

01:44:09.218 --> 01:44:11.935
in the communist system,
you have to applaud;

01:44:11.936 --> 01:44:14.652
in the capitalist system,
you can scream.

01:46:30.601 --> 01:46:34.990
- Hello, Mr. Greenberg.
- Thanks.

01:46:34.991 --> 01:46:35.930
Happy holiday.

01:46:35.931 --> 01:46:38.229
Thank you.
Here let me help you.

01:46:52.127 --> 01:46:54.739
The doorman...

01:46:54.741 --> 01:46:57.247
Hey, let's go.
I've got a break.

01:46:58.083 --> 01:47:00.800
You're writing a novel!

01:47:44.479 --> 01:47:46.047
Laz.

01:48:44.147 --> 01:48:45.923
What happened?

01:48:45.923 --> 01:48:48.953
- Oh, I broke a glass.
- Hey, you're bleeding.

01:48:48.954 --> 01:48:50.416
Leave it alone.
Laz! Laz!

01:48:50.834 --> 01:48:52.193
I'm trying to help.

01:48:54.910 --> 01:48:57.000
What's the matter, Rey?

01:48:58.880 --> 01:49:03.792
You are like a milk cow
that gives milk

01:49:03.793 --> 01:49:06.195
all the time and then
kicks over the bucket.

01:49:10.166 --> 01:49:12.151
There's the door, doorman.

01:49:16.540 --> 01:49:18.944
Walk through it.
Walk through it.

01:49:18.944 --> 01:49:20.093
I don't want to
see you again.

01:49:20.093 --> 01:49:21.974
I'm tired of living
with a moron.

01:49:21.974 --> 01:49:24.482
You are a moron, Laz.

01:49:24.483 --> 01:49:26.781
Please, leave the keys
on the table.

01:50:09.833 --> 01:50:13.908
The moon bathes Death
in a light

01:50:13.909 --> 01:50:16.834
that makes him look
like a white star

01:50:16.835 --> 01:50:20.387
twinkling in the middle
of the backyard.

01:50:24.672 --> 01:50:26.866
That used to be my bicycle.

01:50:52.258 --> 01:50:53.512
Rey!

01:50:54.766 --> 01:50:56.020
Open the door!

01:51:00.305 --> 01:51:01.663
Rey!

01:51:16.188 --> 01:51:17.964
Reinaldo.
Hey, Reinaldo.

01:51:18.487 --> 01:51:20.472
How ya doing?
Come on, get up.

01:51:20.577 --> 01:51:21.308
It's time to go.

01:51:21.309 --> 01:51:23.294
Where?

01:51:23.294 --> 01:51:24.757
It's time to go home.

01:51:24.758 --> 01:51:26.220
Cuba?

01:51:26.221 --> 01:51:29.250
No, I think you should go
to your apartment first.

01:51:29.250 --> 01:51:31.131
Come on, I'll give
you a hand.

01:51:32.803 --> 01:51:34.266
Here we go.

01:51:37.819 --> 01:51:39.490
Are these your
things here?

01:51:39.492 --> 01:51:42.730
How are you feeling?
You feeling alright?

01:51:45.342 --> 01:51:47.223
I can't believe they're
sending you home.

01:51:52.134 --> 01:51:54.329
Do you have any insurance?

01:51:54.330 --> 01:51:56.732
- Yes, I do.
- I don't.

01:51:57.150 --> 01:51:59.867
- Don't forget the plant.
- I won't.

01:57:04.995 --> 01:57:06.980
Hello.

01:57:07.085 --> 01:57:08.652
You got everything?

01:57:08.652 --> 01:57:10.533
Yes.

01:57:10.533 --> 01:57:13.041
Give me a glass...

01:57:15.340 --> 01:57:17.325
and a straw.

01:57:33.731 --> 01:57:35.299
Where is the straw?

01:57:35.299 --> 01:57:38.016
- What?
- Where is the straw?

01:57:38.016 --> 01:57:39.687
The straw, yeah.

01:57:54.003 --> 01:57:55.675
You do it.

01:58:16.888 --> 01:58:19.709
Laz...

01:58:19.710 --> 01:58:23.471
I have something
to show you.

01:58:23.472 --> 01:58:25.979
Look.

01:58:32.040 --> 01:58:34.548
Here's "The Doorman. "

01:58:43.534 --> 01:58:46.042
"For Lazaro, his novel. "

01:58:48.968 --> 01:58:50.536
It just came out.

01:58:50.640 --> 01:58:52.835
You can have
all the money.

01:58:52.836 --> 01:58:53.775
The money?

01:58:55.760 --> 01:58:58.164
It's my book, Rey,

01:58:58.164 --> 01:59:00.776
you took it and now
you're going to insult me

01:59:00.776 --> 01:59:02.135
by paying me for it?

01:59:08.718 --> 01:59:12.062
Okay, sorry.
Thanks.

01:59:12.063 --> 01:59:14.674
- Don't say nothing.
- Okay.

01:59:16.346 --> 01:59:19.794
Give me a glass
with a...

01:59:49.367 --> 01:59:53.547
This bag
is important, Laz.

01:59:53.548 --> 01:59:54.696
You can take it.

01:59:54.696 --> 01:59:57.099
You're going to need
it more than me.

01:59:57.100 --> 01:59:58.667
Take it.

02:00:00.966 --> 02:00:04.101
I want you to promise
me something, Lázaro.

02:00:09.325 --> 02:00:12.669
I don't want to wake up
in the hospital.

02:00:13.714 --> 02:00:14.968
Promise me.

02:00:17.163 --> 02:00:19.253
I promise.

02:00:20.715 --> 02:00:23.746
Sure?

02:00:23.747 --> 02:00:24.791
Yeah.

02:00:27.612 --> 02:00:29.389
Sure?

02:00:32.733 --> 02:00:34.404
Hmmm?

02:00:51.542 --> 02:00:53.214
I'm sorry.

02:01:03.768 --> 02:01:05.231
Yes.

02:01:34.594 --> 02:01:36.579
Give me the glass, please.

02:01:47.969 --> 02:01:50.477
I want you to mail these.

02:01:52.045 --> 02:01:54.866
This is for---

02:01:56.120 --> 02:01:58.210
This is for my mother.

02:02:00.404 --> 02:02:03.210
This is for
"The New York Times, "

02:02:05.185 --> 02:02:07.679
Margarita and Jorge Camacho.

02:02:10.174 --> 02:02:12.980
"Miami Herald. "

02:02:14.435 --> 02:02:19.943
And, this is for you,
but, don't open it.

02:02:19.944 --> 02:02:23.476
Mail this to yourself,

02:02:23.476 --> 02:02:25.347
and then you open
in your house.

02:02:33.038 --> 02:02:43.742
I have never met a boy
as authentic as you, Lázaro.

02:02:44.885 --> 02:02:46.028
Never.

02:02:59.747 --> 02:03:01.825
Read me something.

02:03:25.936 --> 02:03:27.703
Oh, not that one.

02:03:27.703 --> 02:03:29.678
Not that one,
where's the glass?

02:03:32.796 --> 02:03:34.562
Not that one.

02:04:31.722 --> 02:04:34.736
Rey.
Rey.

